
remark  File dihiscu.top
remark    Topology patch to describe the conformation of two histidines
remark    bound to a Cu+2 ion (via their NE2 atoms) in the adjacent equatorial 
remark    positions of a square-pyramidal coordination. 
remark
remark  Use in combination with dihiscu.par.
remark  Use after loading protein-1.0.top.  It loads ion.top.
remark
remark  Author: Guillermo A. Bermejo (03/18/2014).



! Load topology info of ions (we need CU2).
@TOPPAR:ion.top



presidue DIHCU2  ! 1=HIS 2=CU2 3=HIS
   
   delete    atom 1HE2               end
   delete    atom 3HE2               end
   ! modify charges of remaining atoms?

   add bond 1NE2 2CU+2
   add bond 3NE2 2CU+2

   add angle 1NE2 2CU+2 3NE2
   
   add angle 1CD2 1NE2  2CU+2
   add angle 1CE1 1NE2  2CU+2

   add angle 3CD2 3NE2  2CU+2
   add angle 3CE1 3NE2  2CU+2

   add IMPRoper 1NE2  1CD2  1CE1  2CU+2 !planar NE2
   add IMPRoper 3NE2  3CD2  3CE1  2CU+2 !planar NE2
  
end

